place.name: SWINHOPE
place.gazetteerText: SWINHOPE, a parish in Caistor district, Lincoln; 6 miles WSW of North Thoresby r. station, and 7 SE of Caistor. Post town, Grimsby. Acres, 1,307. Real property, £1,866. Pop., 105. houses, 20. The manor, with S. house, belongs to G. M. Alington, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £262.* Patron, G. M. Alington, Esq. The church is ancient. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
